{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"938188ae-271f-46b3-a442-f7a9ef5187fc","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a standard .NET MAUI property — that's likely why it has no effect. Here's what you need:\n\n### iOS\nUse the iOS platform-specific `UseSafeArea` property:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"\n             Padding=\"0\">\n\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### Android\nOn Android 15+ (API 35), apps are edge-to-edge by default. For older versions, opt in from your `MainActivity` or platform code:\n\n```csharp\n// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n}\n```\n\n### Checklist\n1. **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"`** — the real iOS knob (not `SafeAreaEdges`)\n2. **`Padding=\"0\"`** on the page — some templates add default padding\n3. **`Aspect=\"AspectFill\"`** on the `Image` — so it fills rather than letterboxes\n4. **Android edge-to-edge** — `SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false)` for pre-API 35\n\nIf you also want the status/nav bars to be **transparent** on Android, set the bar colors in your theme or via `Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent)`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a59bf885-27f3-4faf-9b4e-e21f515b5e02","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making content go edge-to-edge in a .NET MAUI app, specifically behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but the image still has padding.\n\nThis is a common .NET MAUI question. In .NET MAUI, to achieve true edge-to-edge content:\n\n1. `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` is not a real property on ContentPage in .NET MAUI. The user might be confused with something else.\n\n2. In .NET MAUI for .NET 8+, there are a few approaches:\n   - On iOS, I need to use `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"false\"` to ignore safe area insets\n   - On Android, I need to configure the window and status bar behavior to allow content behind system bars\n\nLet me think through the platform-specific solutions more carefully for the current .NET MAUI versions. I'm realizing `SafeAreaEdges` isn't actually a standard .NET MAUI property—the correct approach on iOS is using the platform-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"`, while Android needs edge-to-edge configuration through `WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows` or built-in support in newer versions. I'm realizing that `SafeAreaEdges` isn't actually a standard MAUI property—the correct approach for iOS is using `UseSafeArea` on the page itself, and I should clarify that for the user with the proper implementation details.","outputTokens":1383,"requestId":"7FCD:1EA6C7:443A1A2:4AC1F23:69F15960"},"id":"ccd6c743-1b18-4515-a884-5076ebc4926e","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:06:02.759Z","parentId":"901d628b-a326-480d-9a84-168d8fd170b0"}
